A man has been arrested in connection with eight incidents of sexual assault and harassment in just one day. The first was reported in the morning and then more were reported in south London as yesterday went on. Police soon linked the reports, which all happened in the Camberwell and Ruskin Park areas of Southwark. A Metropolitan Police spokesman said: ‘An extensive policing plan was implemented, including deploying additional uniformed officers and detectives to the area, speaking to victims and witnesses and checking CCTV.’ A suspect was identified yesterday evening, and arrested on suspicion of sexual assault. He remains in custody. Supt Dan Ivey, Central South Command Unit, said: ‘We’re aware of posts on social media and fully recognise the considerable concern these incidents have caused among the community. ‘We share that concern and are actively investigating with a dedicated team of detectives. ‘A man remains in police custody. Any women who have not yet reported any potential incidents to police are encouraged to do so.’ Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.